    ðŸ”¹ `getfacl -a file` --> ðŸ§¾ Displays all ACL entries, not just user and group.
    ðŸ”¹ `getfacl -d directory` --> ðŸ“‚ Displays the default ACLs of the directory "directory", which are applied to new files and directories created within it.
    ðŸ”¹ `getfacl -p file` --> ðŸ–¨ Displays ACLs in a portable format, suitable for use with `setfacl`.

ðŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ getfacl myfile.txt

    ðŸ”¹ Displays the ACLs of the file "myfile.txt".

    $ getfacl -d mydirectory

    ðŸ”¹ Displays the default ACLs of the directory "mydirectory".

